    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.25.6-8_0001" />
                
                <fw type="curatorial">6</fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        Dalton, Nebr.
                        March 11 - 195<del>6</del><add>7</add>
                    </dateline>
                
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Mr John Neihardt</addrLine>
                            <addrLine>Skyrim Farm Rt. 6</addrLine>
                                <addrLine>Columbia, Mo.</addrLine>
                    </address>
                
                    <salute>Dear John-</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>I thought you might be interested in a letter I recieved recently from Ed Hansen, (son of Pete Hansen, old time section foreman). My <hi rend="caps">H.S.</hi> class; have only contacted him once or twice in past 40 yrs. A strange case&#8212; Ed had a fine mind. Headed class in <hi rend="caps">H.S.</hi> worked a couple of years made <hi rend="caps">A.B.</hi> degree Bellevue in 3 yrs. <unclear>Laugh</unclear> <hi rend="caps">H.S.</hi> a couple of yrs. Summer vacation became <hi rend="double underline">Expert</hi> in Gregg systems short hand. not reelected to <hi rend="caps">H.S.</hi> position Ed went back to Bancroft and became a recluse, living alone in a small shack went to work on <unclear>section</unclear>, later variety of odd jobs was handy with tools &#8212;&#8212;</p>
                
                <p>I just returned home from a 12 day stay in Scottsbluffs, Nebr. Hospital Operation Febr. 26th Prostratectomy, some complications, Thank God, no malignancy formed and am coming along just fine.</p>
                
                <note><unclear reason="scribble"/></note>
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.25.6-8_0002"/>
                
                    <fw type="curatorial">7</fw> 
                    <fw type="authorial">II</fw>
                
                <p>Just one other bit of information from local papers, you might be interested in about a month or six weeks ago.</p>
                    
                <p>Adam Pretty Horse (Sioux). Body found found in an alley on outskirts of Bayard, Nebr shot through the back.</p> 
                
                <p>At inquest, none of Pretty Horse's relatives or companions present, night marshal testified he attempted to stop a quarrel amongst several persons. Pretty Horse started to run away, intendid<sic>intended</sic> to fire a shot in the air to halt him. Pretty Horse's daughter grabbed his arm and <unclear/> his arm. Exonerated&#8212; "performance of duty,," no illegal act,, &#8212; a county seat (Bridgeport) attorney (not the <hi rend="underline">most</hi> reputable these) presented the district judge with a <unclear>petition</unclear> for a Grand Jury investigation many more than required number of signers required by law. So far no action by District Judge except <unclear>writ</unclear> requiring they show further need for investigation.</p> 
                
                <p>Write <hi rend="underline">when the spirit</hi> moves.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>As always</salute>
                    <signed>Rex Carey</signed>
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
            
            
